nodes.title: Links to the upscale models
widgets_values:
Put them into models/upscale_models folder

[2xhigurashi v1 compact](https://openmodeldb.info/models/2x-Higurashi-v1-compact) - this is an anime focused upscaler but fast

[4xClear reality v1](https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-ClearRealityV1) - a fast ppl focused upscaler

[4xDF2K_JPEG](https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-realsr-df2k-jpeg) - a slower but better quality upscaler

[1xDeJPG](https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-DeJPG-realplksr-otf) - one of my favorite enhancer model

[1xSkinContrast Strong](https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-SkinContrast-HighAlternative-SuperUltraCompact) - This model has 3 variations. This one is too strong sometimes

[1xSkinContrast](https://openmodeldb.info/models/1x-SkinContrast-SuperUltraCompact)
Using the image sharpening nodes are faster but sometimes I get better results with image upscaling / downscaling method. Or you can use both.
Use VACE if you want to keep the original likeness. It will be a bit slower and use more VRAM.
Most probably skin detailer isn't necessary during the iterative upscaling process. But feel free to try it and decide yourself.
Connect this node if you don't want to use VACE
